      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the pain is mostly gone and you feel only mild dizziness, you can certainly try managing it at home with more hydration and a good night's sleep. However, since the initial event was so sudden and severe, a quick, proactive check-in with your primary care physician is often the best course of action to rule out anything serious. If you are truly worried, a quick telehealth consult is a much less expensive option than an ER visit.",
      "source": "target",
