      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the episode was truly a one-off spike and is now resolving, managing it with electrolytes and rest is a sensible first step. However, if you are going to take ibuprofen, make sure you are taking it with food to protect your stomach lining. If you find yourself needing to take more than one dose, or if the headache returns with any significant intensity, do not hesitate to seek professional medical advice.",
